    "summary": "I am a PhD student at Leiden Observatory working on radio astronomy and cosmology. My PhD projects cover ionospheric calibration, giant radio galaxies, the synchrotron Milky Way, and the synchrotron Cosmic Web.\nRecently, my team and I have discovered Alcyoneus, a giant radio galaxy of at least 5 megaparsecs (16 million light-years) long, which we report in Astronomy & Astrophysics. At least in projection, this is the largest known structure made by a galaxy! https://arxiv.org/abs/2202.05427\n\nMy main other academic interests are biology, mathematics, and physics.\n\nYou can read more on my website: http://home.strw.leidenuniv.nl/~oei/.",
